\[\cos \theta = \cos 30^\circ + \cos 318^\circ + \cos 102^\circ + \cos 174^\circ.\]If we plot $(\cos t, \sin t)$ for $t = 30^\circ,$ $102^\circ,$ $174^\circ,$ $246^\circ,$ and $318^\circ,$ the five points form the vertices of a regular pentagon.

